    <item>
      <title>How to Manage Your Research Paper Library with Zotero</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/en/posts/2024-11-28-zotero/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 28 Nov 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/posts/2024-11-28-zotero/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;If you’re a researcher, student, or academic drowning in PDFs and journal articles, Zotero might be the tool you didn’t know you needed. It&amp;rsquo;s a powerful, free, and open-source reference manager that helps you collect, organize, annotate, cite, and share your research materials with ease.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this post, we’ll look at how to set up and optimize Zotero for managing a growing library of research papers, especially PDFs. We&amp;rsquo;ll also explore helpful features and best practices to avoid common pitfalls.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
